{
  "stem": "7437.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "At that time, there were a lot-- not a lot, but there were several other survivors in Lutsk.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we all got together, looking for our loved ones and trying to pick up life from the beginning.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Each one of us had a different story.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And yet they were all very similar.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I decided to make my way back to my hometown, again, hoping against hope that I would find my family.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Needless to say, I went back with the other survivor from my hometown, whom I met in Lutsk and who lives now in Duluth, Minnesota, and we went back to my hometown.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And we didn't find anything or anybody.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "The place where the ghetto was, was completely leveled.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Our house, my house, was still there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And of course, all the people around surrounded us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And they kept saying, oh, if only we knew what was going on, if only we knew, they would have helped, obviously.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "That time, I found out that my sister was denounced several days after she went into hiding.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And she was paraded in the nude in the Main Street, tortured.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And then they murdered her.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In my, in my, in my town, yes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Who, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nobody-- well, I had two versions about my father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One version was that they took him in a group of the first-- the people whom they rounded up at first, that they took them to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the other version was that they made them dig a big pit right outside our town.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they killed him right there and then.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Nobody knew or knows anything about the fate of my mother.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There is really no closure to my grief.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
